Quoted By: >>37183812 >>37184752 >>37185649 >>37189652
Intertwining her fingers with his, Eliza Vardroder pushed herself up just enough to make eye contact with her fellow soldier. "Not as bad as you thought, huh?", she said, though it was clear to both of them that it was a rhetorical question. He turned his head to one side without a word, but she grabbed his chin and forced him to look at her again. "C'mon. I can hear by the way your heart beats that you like this. But I want you to say it," she whispered.

A void opened up in his mind - he had no idea how to respond, because his anxiety and fear weren't strong enough to make a decision for him. He was afraid, yes, but the surprisingly gentle contact with the tall woman wasn't anything close to the nightmarish fears he had entertained just an hour earlier. Some of that indecision must have shone through to the wolf, as the hand on his chin slipped down to hold the back of his head, and she went in for a kiss.

Even though he had seen her move her head, it still came as a surprise to him. When her lips met his, when her wide tongue passed them and began to intertwine with his own, he was overwhelmed by the sheer sensations. Taste, smell, touch, all were clamoring for his attention, and for a few seconds, he became completely lost in them. Then she pulled back, and he was shocked to realize that he missed her. That single fact shook him harder than anything else he had endured today, and he found himself unable to do anything but stare up at Vardroder, who was looking down at him with their faces just a hands' width apart.

"So?“

That word brought him back to reality, and even though he found it hard to admit - she was right. Not only had the brief contact stilled his fears, it had even felt good, completely unlike anything he'd ever felt before.

He had liked it, and he wanted more.
